      "rawMarkdown": "# 95. Disparate\n\n**Pronunciation:** DIS-puh-rit\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Very different in kind; not comparable.\n**Bangla meaning:** ভিন্ন প্রকৃতির, সম্পূর্ণ আলাদা, অসদৃশ\n**Root story:** From Latin *disparatus* / *dispar* = unequal, unlike.\n**Simple explanation:** Disparate things are so different that they do not naturally belong together.\n**Memory hook:** **Disparate = different parts.**\n**GRE synonyms:** distinct, divergent, dissimilar, unlike, heterogeneous\n**Basic synonyms:** different, separate, varied\n**Antonyms:** similar, alike, homogeneous, identical\n**Common usage:** disparate groups, disparate ideas, disparate data, disparate sources\n**Confusing word:** Disparate ≠ Desperate. **Disparate** = different; **desperate** = hopeless or urgent.\n**Final memory:** **Disparate = fundamentally different = ভিন্ন প্রকৃতির**\n\n## Examples\n\n### Easy Examples\n\n1. The two books have disparate themes.\n   Meaning: Their themes are very different.\n   Bangla: বিষয়গুলো ভিন্ন।\n\n2. The class included students from disparate backgrounds.\n   Meaning: The students came from different backgrounds.\n   Bangla: ভিন্ন পটভূমি।\n\n3. The two reports gave disparate results.\n   Meaning: The results did not match.\n   Bangla: ফলাফল আলাদা।\n\n### GRE / Academic Examples\n\n4. The researcher combined disparate datasets into one model.\n   Meaning: The datasets were different in type or source.\n   Bangla: ভিন্ন ধরনের তথ্য একত্র করা।\n\n5. The committee struggled to reconcile disparate opinions.\n   Meaning: The opinions were very different.\n   Bangla: ভিন্ন মত মিলানো কঠিন।\n\n6. Disparate economic conditions produced unequal outcomes across regions.\n   Meaning: Different conditions caused different results.\n   Bangla: ভিন্ন অর্থনৈতিক অবস্থা ভিন্ন ফল দেয়।\n\n7. The theory connects seemingly disparate phenomena under one explanation.\n   Meaning: It links things that appear unrelated.\n   Bangla: আলাদা ঘটনাকে এক ব্যাখ্যায় যুক্ত করা।\n\n### Real-World / Paper-Style Examples\n\n8. In engineering research, disparate sensor readings may indicate calibration problems.\n   Meaning: Different readings may show measurement error.\n   Bangla: সেন্সর রিডিং ভিন্ন হলে সমস্যা হতে পারে।\n\n9. In social science, disparate communities often experience policies differently.\n   Meaning: Different groups are affected differently.\n   Bangla: ভিন্ন সম্প্রদায়ের অভিজ্ঞতা ভিন্ন।\n\n10. In machine learning, models trained on disparate datasets may generalize poorly.\n    Meaning: Very different data can reduce model reliability.\n    Bangla: ভিন্ন ডেটা মডেলের ফল খারাপ করতে পারে।\n\n## GRE Synonym Examples\n\n1. The two proposals were **distinct** in purpose.\n2. Their political views were **divergent**.\n3. The samples were chemically **dissimilar**.\n4. The twins had **unlike** personalities.\n5. The population was **heterogeneous**.\n6. The categories must remain **distinct**.\n7. The studies reached **divergent** conclusions.\n8. The products were visually similar but functionally **dissimilar**.\n9. The two cultures were **unlike** in social structure.\n10. The classroom was intellectually **heterogeneous**.\n11. The researcher separated **distinct** variables.\n12. Economic interests became increasingly **divergent**.\n13. The materials were **dissimilar** in strength.\n14. The two cases were legally **unlike**.\n15. The committee represented a **heterogeneous** mix of professions.\n\n---",
