      "rawMarkdown": "# 100. Garrulous\n\n**Pronunciation:** GAR-yuh-ləs\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Excessively talkative, especially about unimportant things.\n**Bangla meaning:** অতিরিক্ত বাচাল, বেশি কথা বলে এমন\n**Root story:** From Latin *garrire* = to chatter.\n**Simple explanation:** A garrulous person talks too much, often in a rambling or annoying way.\n**Memory hook:** **Garrulous = garage full of talk.**\n**GRE synonyms:** talkative, chatty, loquacious, verbose, voluble\n**Basic synonyms:** wordy, talky, babbling\n**Antonyms:** taciturn, reserved, silent, reticent\n**Common usage:** garrulous old man, garrulous speaker, garrulous host, garrulous conversation\n**Confusing word:** Garrulous ≠ Gregarious. **Garrulous** = talks too much; **gregarious** = sociable.\n**Final memory:** **Garrulous = too talkative = অতিরিক্ত বাচাল**\n\n## Examples\n\n### Easy Examples\n\n1. My uncle is garrulous.\n   Meaning: He talks too much.\n   Bangla: তিনি খুব বেশি কথা বলেন।\n\n2. The garrulous passenger talked all night.\n   Meaning: The passenger kept talking.\n   Bangla: যাত্রীটি সারারাত কথা বলেছে।\n\n3. She became garrulous after tea.\n   Meaning: She started talking a lot.\n   Bangla: চা খাওয়ার পর বেশি কথা বলল।\n\n### GRE / Academic Examples\n\n4. The garrulous witness gave many irrelevant details.\n   Meaning: The witness talked too much.\n   Bangla: অপ্রাসঙ্গিক কথা বেশি বলল।\n\n5. A garrulous lecturer may obscure the main argument.\n   Meaning: Too much talk can hide the main point.\n   Bangla: বেশি কথা মূল যুক্তি ঢেকে দেয়।\n\n6. The interviewer struggled to redirect the garrulous candidate.\n   Meaning: The candidate talked too much.\n   Bangla: প্রার্থী বেশি কথা বলছিল।\n\n7. The report criticized the speech as garrulous rather than persuasive.\n   Meaning: It was wordy, not convincing.\n   Bangla: বক্তৃতা বাচাল, প্রভাবশালী নয়।\n\n### Real-World / Paper-Style Examples\n\n8. In workplace communication, garrulous meetings can reduce productivity.\n   Meaning: Excessive talk wastes time.\n   Bangla: বেশি কথা উৎপাদনশীলতা কমায়।\n\n9. In legal settings, a garrulous witness may confuse the timeline.\n   Meaning: Too much detail can create confusion.\n   Bangla: অতিরিক্ত কথা সময়রেখা অস্পষ্ট করে।\n\n10. In academic presentations, garrulous explanations can weaken clarity.\n    Meaning: Wordiness can reduce understanding.\n    Bangla: অতিরিক্ত ব্যাখ্যা স্পষ্টতা কমায়।\n\n## GRE Synonym Examples\n\n1. The **talkative** child asked many questions.\n2. The **chatty** host entertained everyone.\n3. The **loquacious** professor rarely paused.\n4. His **verbose** answer annoyed the panel.\n5. The **voluble** speaker answered rapidly.\n6. A **talkative** employee can energize or distract a team.\n7. The **chatty** neighbor shared every detail.\n8. The **loquacious** salesman dominated the conversation.\n9. The memo was too **verbose**.\n10. The politician was unusually **voluble** during the debate.\n11. The **talkative** guide described every building.\n12. The **chatty** tone made the article informal.\n13. The **loquacious** guest prevented others from speaking.\n14. The report’s **verbose** style obscured its findings.\n15. The **voluble** witness overwhelmed the jury with details.\n\n---",
