      "rawMarkdown": "# 101. Incendiary\n\n**Pronunciation:** in-SEN-dee-air-ee\n**Part of speech:** Adjective / Noun\n**Core meaning:** Designed to cause fire or provoke conflict.\n**Bangla meaning:** উত্তেজক, অগ্নিসংযোগকারী, সংঘাত উসকে দেয় এমন\n**Root story:** From Latin *incendere* = to set on fire.\n**Simple explanation:** Incendiary can mean physically causing fire or emotionally/politically causing anger and conflict.\n**Memory hook:** **Incendiary = ignite anger or fire.**\n**GRE synonyms:** inflammatory, provocative, seditious, combustible, agitational\n**Basic synonyms:** explosive, fire-starting, anger-causing\n**Antonyms:** calming, conciliatory, soothing, pacifying\n**Common usage:** incendiary speech, incendiary device, incendiary rhetoric, incendiary accusation\n**Confusing word:** Incendiary ≠ Ordinary. **Incendiary** means fire-starting or conflict-provoking.\n**Final memory:** **Incendiary = sets fire or provokes anger = উত্তেজক**\n\n## Examples\n\n### Easy Examples\n\n1. The police found an incendiary device.\n   Meaning: It was made to start a fire.\n   Bangla: অগ্নিসংযোগকারী যন্ত্র।\n\n2. His words were incendiary.\n   Meaning: His words provoked anger.\n   Bangla: কথাগুলো উত্তেজক ছিল।\n\n3. The article used incendiary language.\n   Meaning: It tried to inflame emotions.\n   Bangla: উত্তেজনামূলক ভাষা।\n\n### GRE / Academic Examples\n\n4. The politician’s incendiary remarks deepened social division.\n   Meaning: His remarks increased conflict.\n   Bangla: উত্তেজক মন্তব্য বিভাজন বাড়াল।\n\n5. The editorial avoided incendiary claims and relied on evidence.\n   Meaning: It avoided provocative language.\n   Bangla: উত্তেজক দাবি এড়ানো।\n\n6. Incendiary rhetoric can transform disagreement into hostility.\n   Meaning: Provocative speech can create conflict.\n   Bangla: উত্তেজক ভাষা বিরোধ বাড়ায়।\n\n7. The court examined whether the speech was merely offensive or genuinely incendiary.\n   Meaning: The court asked if it could provoke conflict.\n   Bangla: বক্তব্যটি সত্যিই উত্তেজক কি না।\n\n### Real-World / Paper-Style Examples\n\n8. In political communication, incendiary slogans can mobilize supporters but polarize society.\n   Meaning: Strong slogans can energize and divide.\n   Bangla: স্লোগান সমাজকে বিভক্ত করতে পারে।\n\n9. In security reports, incendiary materials are treated as major public safety risks.\n   Meaning: Fire-causing materials are dangerous.\n   Bangla: অগ্নিসংযোগকারী উপাদান ঝুঁকিপূর্ণ।\n\n10. In online discourse, incendiary posts often spread faster than balanced analysis.\n    Meaning: Provocative content attracts attention.\n    Bangla: উত্তেজক পোস্ট দ্রুত ছড়ায়।\n\n## GRE Synonym Examples\n\n1. The article’s **inflammatory** tone angered readers.\n2. His **provocative** question disrupted the meeting.\n3. The rebels distributed **seditious** pamphlets.\n4. Dry leaves are highly **combustible**.\n5. The speech had an **agitational** purpose.\n6. The leader avoided **inflammatory** language.\n7. The professor asked a **provocative** question to start debate.\n8. The regime banned **seditious** writing.\n9. The chemical was dangerously **combustible**.\n10. The campaign used **agitational** rhetoric.\n11. **Inflammatory** rumors spread quickly.\n12. The film made a **provocative** political argument.\n13. Authorities feared the message was **seditious**.\n14. The storage room contained **combustible** material.\n15. The pamphlet’s **agitational** tone encouraged protest.\n\n---",
