      "rawMarkdown": "# 102. Inimical\n\n**Pronunciation:** ih-NIM-i-kəl\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Harmful, hostile, or unfriendly.\n**Bangla meaning:** ক্ষতিকর, শত্রুভাবাপন্ন, বিরূপ\n**Root story:** From Latin *inimicus*: *in-* = not + *amicus* = friend. So inimical means “not friendly.”\n**Simple explanation:** Something inimical opposes, harms, or works against something else.\n**Memory hook:** **Inimical = enemy-like.**\n**GRE synonyms:** hostile, adverse, antagonistic, detrimental, deleterious\n**Basic synonyms:** harmful, unfriendly, opposing\n**Antonyms:** friendly, beneficial, favorable, supportive\n**Common usage:** inimical to health, inimical to democracy, inimical forces, inimical environment\n**Confusing word:** Inimical ≠ Inimitable. **Inimical** = harmful/hostile; **inimitable** = impossible to imitate.\n**Final memory:** **Inimical = harmful or hostile = ক্ষতিকর / শত্রুভাবাপন্ন**\n\n## Examples\n\n### Easy Examples\n\n1. Smoking is inimical to health.\n   Meaning: Smoking harms health.\n   Bangla: ধূমপান স্বাস্থ্যের জন্য ক্ষতিকর।\n\n2. His attitude was inimical to teamwork.\n   Meaning: His attitude harmed teamwork.\n   Bangla: দলগত কাজের জন্য বিরূপ।\n\n3. The cold climate was inimical to the plants.\n   Meaning: The climate damaged the plants.\n   Bangla: গাছের জন্য ক্ষতিকর।\n\n### GRE / Academic Examples\n\n4. Corruption is inimical to institutional trust.\n   Meaning: It damages trust in institutions.\n   Bangla: দুর্নীতি প্রতিষ্ঠানের আস্থা নষ্ট করে।\n\n5. The policy was criticized as inimical to small businesses.\n   Meaning: It harmed small businesses.\n   Bangla: ছোট ব্যবসার জন্য ক্ষতিকর।\n\n6. Censorship is inimical to open academic inquiry.\n   Meaning: It opposes free research and discussion.\n   Bangla: মুক্ত গবেষণার বিরোধী।\n\n7. Extreme inequality can be inimical to social stability.\n   Meaning: It can damage social peace.\n   Bangla: সামাজিক স্থিতির জন্য ক্ষতিকর।\n\n### Real-World / Paper-Style Examples\n\n8. In environmental science, pollution is inimical to aquatic ecosystems.\n   Meaning: Pollution harms water life.\n   Bangla: জলজ পরিবেশের জন্য ক্ষতিকর।\n\n9. In economics, unstable regulation can be inimical to long-term investment.\n   Meaning: Uncertainty discourages investment.\n   Bangla: দীর্ঘমেয়াদি বিনিয়োগের জন্য বিরূপ।\n\n10. In education policy, rote learning may be inimical to critical thinking.\n    Meaning: Memorization-only learning can harm reasoning.\n    Bangla: মুখস্থনির্ভর শিক্ষা চিন্তাশক্তির ক্ষতি করে।\n\n## GRE Synonym Examples\n\n1. The two nations had **hostile** relations.\n2. The medicine caused **adverse** effects.\n3. His tone was openly **antagonistic**.\n4. The policy was **detrimental** to growth.\n5. The chemical had **deleterious** effects.\n6. The witness faced a **hostile** courtroom.\n7. The project suffered from **adverse** weather.\n8. The debate became **antagonistic**.\n9. Poor nutrition is **detrimental** to development.\n10. Air pollution is **deleterious** to lung function.\n11. The manager created a **hostile** workplace.\n12. The data revealed **adverse** trends.\n13. His **antagonistic** behavior weakened cooperation.\n14. Excessive debt can be **detrimental** to stability.\n15. The toxin was **deleterious** to wildlife.\n\n---",
