      "rawMarkdown": "# 104. Invigorate\n\n**Pronunciation:** in-VIG-uh-rayt\n**Part of speech:** Verb\n**Core meaning:** To give energy, strength, or life.\n**Bangla meaning:** চাঙ্গা করা, শক্তি দেওয়া, প্রাণবন্ত করা\n**Root story:** From Latin *in-* = into + *vigor* = strength, liveliness.\n**Simple explanation:** To invigorate means to refresh, energize, or make something active again.\n**Memory hook:** **Invigorate = put vigor in.**\n**GRE synonyms:** energize, animate, revitalize, stimulate, rejuvenate\n**Basic synonyms:** refresh, strengthen, wake up, renew\n**Antonyms:** enervate, weaken, drain, exhaust\n**Common usage:** invigorate the economy, invigorate debate, invigorate the body, invigorate reform\n**Confusing word:** Invigorate ≠ Enervate. **Invigorate** = give energy; **enervate** = drain energy.\n**Final memory:** **Invigorate = fill with energy = চাঙ্গা করা**\n\n## Examples\n\n### Easy Examples\n\n1. A cold shower invigorated him.\n   Meaning: It refreshed him.\n   Bangla: ঠান্ডা পানি তাকে চাঙ্গা করল।\n\n2. Exercise invigorates the body.\n   Meaning: Exercise gives energy.\n   Bangla: ব্যায়াম শরীর চাঙ্গা করে।\n\n3. The music invigorated the crowd.\n   Meaning: The crowd became energetic.\n   Bangla: গান সবাইকে উজ্জীবিত করল।\n\n### GRE / Academic Examples\n\n4. The reform was designed to invigorate local businesses.\n   Meaning: It aimed to strengthen business activity.\n   Bangla: স্থানীয় ব্যবসাকে চাঙ্গা করা।\n\n5. New evidence invigorated the debate.\n   Meaning: Evidence made the debate active again.\n   Bangla: নতুন প্রমাণ বিতর্ককে প্রাণবন্ত করল।\n\n6. The teacher’s questions invigorated classroom discussion.\n   Meaning: Questions made discussion lively.\n   Bangla: প্রশ্ন আলোচনাকে সক্রিয় করল।\n\n7. Investment in infrastructure can invigorate regional economies.\n   Meaning: It can energize economic growth.\n   Bangla: অবকাঠামো বিনিয়োগ অর্থনীতি চাঙ্গা করে।\n\n### Real-World / Paper-Style Examples\n\n8. In urban planning, green spaces can invigorate neighborhoods socially and economically.\n   Meaning: Parks can make areas more active.\n   Bangla: সবুজ স্থান এলাকা প্রাণবন্ত করে।\n\n9. In education research, project-based learning may invigorate student engagement.\n   Meaning: It can make students more active.\n   Bangla: প্রকল্পভিত্তিক শিক্ষা আগ্রহ বাড়ায়।\n\n10. In policy analysis, competition is often expected to invigorate innovation.\n    Meaning: Competition can stimulate new ideas.\n    Bangla: প্রতিযোগিতা উদ্ভাবন বাড়ায়।\n\n## GRE Synonym Examples\n\n1. Coffee **energized** the workers.\n2. The speech **animated** the audience.\n3. The reforms **revitalized** the economy.\n4. The discovery **stimulated** debate.\n5. The vacation **rejuvenated** her.\n6. Good leadership **energized** the team.\n7. The storyteller **animated** the dull meeting.\n8. New funding **revitalized** the project.\n9. The question **stimulated** further research.\n10. The treatment **rejuvenated** damaged skin.\n11. Training **energized** the volunteers.\n12. The actor’s performance **animated** the scene.\n13. The policy **revitalized** rural markets.\n14. The seminar **stimulated** intellectual curiosity.\n15. Rest **rejuvenated** the exhausted students.\n\n---",
