      "rawMarkdown": "# 105. Mitigate\n\n**Pronunciation:** MIT-uh-gayt\n**Part of speech:** Verb\n**Core meaning:** To make something less severe, harmful, or painful.\n**Bangla meaning:** প্রশমিত করা, ক্ষতি কমানো, তীব্রতা হ্রাস করা\n**Root story:** From Latin *mitigare*: *mitis* = mild + *agere* = to make/do. So mitigate means “to make milder.”\n**Simple explanation:** To mitigate a problem means to reduce its damage, intensity, or seriousness.\n**Memory hook:** **Mitigate = make it mild.**\n**GRE synonyms:** lessen, alleviate, attenuate, reduce, assuage\n**Basic synonyms:** ease, soften, decrease, relieve\n**Antonyms:** worsen, aggravate, intensify, exacerbate\n**Common usage:** mitigate risk, mitigate damage, mitigate suffering, mitigate climate change\n**Confusing word:** Mitigate ≠ Militate. **Mitigate** = reduce severity; **militate against** = work against.\n**Final memory:** **Mitigate = make less severe = প্রশমিত করা**\n\n## Examples\n\n### Easy Examples\n\n1. Medicine mitigated the pain.\n   Meaning: Medicine reduced the pain.\n   Bangla: ওষুধ ব্যথা কমাল।\n\n2. Trees can mitigate heat.\n   Meaning: Trees can reduce heat.\n   Bangla: গাছ গরম কমাতে পারে।\n\n3. The apology mitigated her anger.\n   Meaning: The apology made her less angry.\n   Bangla: ক্ষমা চাওয়া রাগ কমাল।\n\n### GRE / Academic Examples\n\n4. The policy was designed to mitigate economic inequality.\n   Meaning: It aimed to reduce inequality.\n   Bangla: অর্থনৈতিক বৈষম্য কমানো।\n\n5. Engineers added safety systems to mitigate risk.\n   Meaning: Systems reduced possible danger.\n   Bangla: ঝুঁকি কমানোর ব্যবস্থা।\n\n6. Early intervention can mitigate the effects of disease.\n   Meaning: Early action reduces harm.\n   Bangla: দ্রুত ব্যবস্থা ক্ষতি কমায়।\n\n7. The court considered factors that might mitigate the defendant’s responsibility.\n   Meaning: Some factors could reduce blame.\n   Bangla: দায় কমাতে পারে এমন বিষয়।\n\n### Real-World / Paper-Style Examples\n\n8. In climate policy, renewable energy is promoted to mitigate greenhouse gas emissions.\n   Meaning: Clean energy can reduce emissions.\n   Bangla: গ্রিনহাউস গ্যাস কমানো।\n\n9. In disaster management, early warning systems mitigate loss of life.\n   Meaning: Warnings reduce deaths.\n   Bangla: আগাম সতর্কতা প্রাণহানি কমায়।\n\n10. In engineering design, insulation can mitigate heat loss in buildings.\n    Meaning: Insulation reduces energy loss.\n    Bangla: তাপ ক্ষতি কমানো।\n\n## GRE Synonym Examples\n\n1. The new rule **lessened** confusion.\n2. The medicine **alleviated** symptoms.\n3. Distance **attenuated** the signal.\n4. The reform **reduced** corruption.\n5. Her words **assuaged** his fear.\n6. Better drainage **lessened** flood damage.\n7. Food aid **alleviated** hunger.\n8. The wall **attenuated** the noise.\n9. Training **reduced** workplace accidents.\n10. The apology **assuaged** public anger.\n11. The policy **lessened** economic pressure.\n12. Painkillers **alleviated** discomfort.\n13. The vaccine **attenuated** disease severity.\n14. The filter **reduced** pollutants.\n15. The leader’s promise **assuaged** anxiety.\n\n---\n\n# Compact Revision Table — Day 4 Part 1\n\n| No. | Word        | Core Meaning              | Bangla               | High-Value Synonyms       | Antonym     |\n| --: | ----------- | ------------------------- | -------------------- | ------------------------- | ----------- |\n|  91 | Abstain     | avoid doing something     | বিরত থাকা            | refrain, desist, forbear  | indulge     |\n|  92 | Approbation | approval or praise        | অনুমোদন              | endorsement, commendation | disapproval |\n|  93 | Cherish     | value deeply              | লালন করা             | treasure, revere, prize   | neglect     |\n|  94 | Corroborate | support with evidence     | প্রমাণ দ্বারা সমর্থন | verify, substantiate      | refute      |\n|  95 | Disparate   | very different            | ভিন্ন প্রকৃতির       | divergent, dissimilar     | similar     |\n|  96 | Emulate     | imitate to equal/surpass  | অনুসরণ করা           | imitate, mimic, rival     | reject      |\n|  97 | Enervate    | weaken or drain energy    | দুর্বল করা           | debilitate, sap           | invigorate  |\n|  98 | Ephemeral   | short-lived               | ক্ষণস্থায়ী           | fleeting, transient       | permanent   |\n|  99 | Fervid      | intensely passionate      | প্রবল আবেগপূর্ণ      | ardent, zealous           | apathetic   |\n| 100 | Garrulous   | excessively talkative     | অতিরিক্ত বাচাল       | loquacious, verbose       | taciturn    |\n| 101 | Incendiary  | fire-starting/provocative | উত্তেজক              | inflammatory, provocative | calming     |\n| 102 | Inimical    | harmful or hostile        | ক্ষতিকর              | adverse, detrimental      | beneficial  |\n| 103 | Intimate    | hint indirectly           | আভাস দেওয়া           | imply, insinuate          | declare     |\n| 104 | Invigorate  | energize                  | চাঙ্গা করা           | revitalize, stimulate     | enervate    |\n| 105 | Mitigate    | reduce severity           | প্রশমিত করা          | alleviate, lessen         | exacerbate  |\n\n---\n\n## Revision Focus for Tonight\n\nRead these in pairs because they are easy to confuse:\n\n**Abstain vs Indulge**\nAbstain = avoid; indulge = allow yourself to enjoy.\n\n**Enervate vs Invigorate**\nEnervate = weaken; invigorate = energize.\n\n**Disparate vs Desperate**\nDisparate = different; desperate = hopeless/urgent.\n\n**Garrulous vs Taciturn**\nGarrulous = talks too much; taciturn = talks very little.\n\n**Intimate vs Intimate**\nVerb: intimate = hint.\nAdjective: intimate = close/personal.\n\nThe full **40+ question Day 4 quiz** should come after **Part 2: Words 106–120**, because the quiz needs to cover all 30 Day 4 words properly.\n\n\n# Day 4 GRE Vocabulary — Part 2\n\n## Words 106–120\n\nThis completes **Day 4 = Words 91–120**, following your 30-word group structure and the required full-section vocabulary format. Your saved file also says Group/Day 4 maps to **Words 91–120**, and each word card should preserve full sections such as meaning, Bangla, root story, synonyms, antonyms, examples, GRE synonym examples, and final memory. \n\n## Word List — Part 2\n\n106. Obsolete\n107. Opaque\n108. Paradigmatic\n109. Pedantic\n110. Placid\n111. Polemical\n112. Precipitate\n113. Profundity\n114. Prophetic\n115. Prudent\n116. Punctilious\n117. Recondite\n118. Scrupulous\n119. Tranquil\n120. Vacillate\n\n---",
